                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "s4",
            "bg_color": "#44aade",
            "text": {
                "header": "Teamwork",
                "body": "<p>In a typical month, you might build a few media plans for some huge campaigns. Or you might be working on a ton of smaller campaigns at the same time.</p><p>That's why knowing how your team works together is critical. Teamwork is an important part of making the dream work. Knowing who handles what will help to start building trust between you and your pod. </p>",
                "class": "align-right"
            },
            "enter": [
                {
                    "id": "solo-bass",
                    "type": "from",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0
                    }
                }
            ],
            "leave": [
                {
                    "id": "solo-bass",
                    "type": "to",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "s5",
            "bg_color": "#44aade",
            "text": {
                "header": "Third Party Media Plans &<br>Media Buying Systems",
                "body": "<p>Third party media plans are a common ask from clients during the media planning process. <b>Third party media plan templates</b> are also known as agency spec sheets. Many larger agencies might request us to format our media plans with their templates. That's so they can compare media plans across publishers without worrying about formatting issues. They want to make the metrics, products and budgets easy to compare across media plans. </p><p>Clients might also ask us to build media plans right into their own order management system. Just like we use Slingshot to make media planning easy, clients might use their own system too. Some examples of media planning systems they might use include STRATA, MediaOcean and Prisma. </p><p>In your pod, the campaign specialist handles both of these tasks. </p>",
                "class": "align-center-wide"
            },
            "enter": [
                {
                    "id": "mic",
                    "type": "from",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0,
                        "right": "80%",
                        "ease": "Back.easeOut"
                    }
                }
            ],
            "leave": [
                {
                    "id": "mic",
                    "type": "to",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        
        {
            "id": "s6",
            "bg_color": "#993333",
            "text": {
                "header": "Media Planning Resources",
                "body": "<p>Knowing who handles what task is only half the battle. Lucky for you we have tons of tools and resources to help you develop the best media plans for your clients. </p><p class='pt-callout'>Click on each instrument for more details.</p>",
                "class": "align-left"
            },
            "interaction": {
                "name": "cr_mediaplans_s6",
                "id": "cr-mediaplans-s6",
                "type": "clickReveal",
                "items": [
                    {
                        "header": "Product Guides",
                        "body": "<p><a href='https://pandora.my.salesforce.com/sfc/#workspaceView?selectedWorkspaceId=05840000000HBNZ' target='_blank'>These documents</a> provide features, benefits, advertising objectives and specifications for our products. You can find them in the Salesforce Libraries.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "Avails Tool",
                        "body": "<p>Use <a href='http://slingshot/aap/slingshot/forecast' target='_blank'>this tool</a> for quick spot checks of the available impression inventory. You'll get real-time avails data to help with client conversations.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "Slingshot",
                        "body": "<p>Your <a href='http://slingshot/aap/slingshot/login?next=/slingshot/' target='_blank'>main tool</a> to build media plans. It’s also where you’ll go to pull avails for your entire order. You can even submit pricing approval requests, all in one place.</p>"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "enter": [
                {
                    "id": "cr-mediaplans-s6",
