        {
            "id": "s7",
            "bg_color": "#993333",
            "text": {
                "header": "Pandora Media Plan Workflow",
                "body": "<p>The basic workflow for creating a media plan in Slingshot can be different for each media plan. Why? A big reason is it depends if you're building a Pandora media plan, or a media plan that uses an agency spec sheet. Let's try to figure out the core steps in the process!</p><p class='pt-callout'>First, let's learn about the Pandora Media Plan. Click the lights to uncover more details about each step of the workflow.</p>",
                "class": "align-right"
            },
            "interaction": {
                "name": "cr_mediaplans_s7",
                "id": "cr-mediaplans-s7",
                "type": "clickReveal",
                "items": [
                    {
                        "header": "Step 1: Create Media Plan and Pull Avails in Slingshot",
                        "body": "<p>Campaign specialists plan out line items in Slingshot and pull the avails. That's how you figure out the percentage of inventory that's still available. Work with your pod to recommend revisions. Afterwards campaign specialists make the appropriate revisions to the media plan.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "Step 2: Revise Media Plan and Re-Pull Avails in Slingshot",
                        "body": "<p>Some line items in your plan might not have enough inventory for your budget. Revise these line items and re-pull the impressions within Slingshot. You might need to revise your media plan a few times. </p><p>Afterwards, the account strategist or account executive sends it to the client. Media plan revisions can also occur after client feedback.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "Step 3: Recheck Avails after getting all Insertion Order signatures ",
                        "body": "<p>After everyone's signed the insertion order, campaign specialists recheck impression inventory. This is to make sure that the inventory is still available to book in Slingshot.</p>"
                    }
                ]
            },
